---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import HeroSection from '../components/HeroSection.astro';
import CTAButton from '../components/CTAButton.astro';
import BookingButton from '../components/BookingButton.astro';
import BenefitCard from '../components/BenefitCard.astro';
import { Zap, Lightbulb, Heart, Check, FlaskConical } from '@lucide/astro';
import FAQSection from '../components/FAQSection.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="NAD+ IV Therapy"
  description="NAD+ is a coenzyme central to cellular energy, DNA repair and healthy-aging research. Learn about NAD+ IV therapy in Halifax."
  focusKeyword="NAD therapy Halifax"
>
  <HeroSection
    title="NAD+ IV Therapy"
    compact
    image={{ src: "/images/treatments/nad-iv-therapy-session.webp", alt: "Patient receiving NAD+ IV therapy in Halifax", aspect: "video" }}
  >
    <p>NAD+ (nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide) is a coenzyme essential for cellular energy production, DNA repair and cellular signaling. IV therapy offers a direct way to receive NAD+ and is commonly explored for energy, mental clarity, recovery and healthy-aging support.</p>
  </HeroSection>

  <!-- Three Benefits Section -->
  <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-[#f7f7f5]">
    <div class="section-shell">
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6 lg:gap-8">
        <BenefitCard title="Cellular Energy">
          <Zap slot="icon" class="h-6 w-6" stroke-width={1.75} aria-hidden="true" />
          <p>NAD+ is essential for mitochondrial function and ATP production, helping cells convert nutrients into usable energy.<sup>1-3</sup></p>
        </BenefitCard>

        <BenefitCard title="Mental Clarity">
          <Lightbulb slot="icon" class="h-6 w-6" stroke-width={1.75} aria-hidden="true" />
          <p>NAD+ is important to neuronal metabolism and cellular repair, which has made cognition and brain health an active area of NAD+ research.<sup>3-5</sup></p>
        </BenefitCard>

        <BenefitCard title="Healthy Aging">
          <Heart slot="icon" class="h-6 w-6" stroke-width={1.75} aria-hidden="true" />
          <p>NAD+ supports sirtuins and other enzymes involved in metabolism, stress response and DNA repair—pathways closely studied in healthy aging.<sup>1-5</sup></p>
        </BenefitCard>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What is NAD+ Section -->
  <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-emerald-50">
    <div class="section-shell">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-serif font-medium text-emerald-950 mb-6">What is NAD+?</h2>
          <div class="prose prose-lg text-slate-600">
            <p>
              NAD+ (nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide) is a coenzyme present throughout the body. It helps transfer electrons during energy metabolism and is used by enzymes involved in cellular signaling and DNA repair.
            </p>
            <p>
              NAD+ levels and metabolism change with age, which has led to growing interest in NAD+ for energy, metabolic health, cognition and healthy aging.<sup>1-5</sup> Research includes cell and animal studies as well as a developing body of human work on NAD+ and its precursors.
            </p>
            <p>
              IV administration bypasses the digestive system and delivers NAD+ directly into the bloodstream. This direct route and the ability to individualize the dose and infusion rate are key reasons patients choose NAD+ IV therapy.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl overflow-hidden shadow-xl">
          <img
            src="/images/treatments/nad-cellular-energy.webp"
            width="1200"
            height="654"
            loading="lazy"
            decoding="async"
            alt="Active woman enjoying outdoor activities with renewed energy from NAD+ therapy"
            class="w-full h-full object-cover"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Reasons patients ask section -->
  <section id="conditions-treated" class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-white">
    <div class="section-shell">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-serif font-medium text-emerald-950 mb-4">Why Patients Explore NAD+ Therapy</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          NAD+ IV therapy is commonly explored for energy, mental clarity, recovery and healthy-aging goals.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-start">
        <div class="bg-emerald-50 rounded-2xl p-8 card-hover">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-serif font-medium text-emerald-950 mb-4">Energy and Recovery</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">People often seek NAD+ therapy for low energy, demanding schedules, post-viral fatigue, athletic recovery or periods when they feel depleted.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-emerald-50 rounded-2xl p-8 card-hover">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-serif font-medium text-emerald-950 mb-4">Mental Clarity</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">Brain fog, reduced focus and mental fatigue are common reasons patients are interested in NAD+ and its role in neuronal energy metabolism.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-emerald-50 rounded-2xl p-8 card-hover">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-serif font-medium text-emerald-950 mb-4">Healthy-Aging Interest</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">NAD+ is closely studied in aging, metabolism and cellular repair. Patients often explore it as part of a broader plan for maintaining energy and function over time.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-emerald-50 rounded-2xl p-8 card-hover">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-serif font-medium text-emerald-950 mb-4">Recovery and Wellness</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">NAD+ therapy is also used by patients interested in exercise recovery, resilience during stressful periods, sleep quality and overall vitality.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How NAD+ Works Section -->
  <section id="how-nad-works" class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-emerald-950">
    <div class="section-shell">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-serif font-medium text-white mb-6">How Does NAD+ Work?</h2>
        <div class="prose prose-lg prose-invert">
          <p class="text-white/90">
            NAD+ functions as a critical coenzyme in cellular metabolism, shuttling electrons between molecules during energy production in the mitochondria. Without adequate NAD+, your cells cannot efficiently convert nutrients into usable energy (ATP).<sup>1-3</sup>
          </p>
          <p class="text-white/90">
            Beyond energy production, NAD+ is required by sirtuins and PARP enzymes involved in metabolism, stress response, cellular signaling and DNA repair.<sup>1-3</sup>
          </p>
          <p class="text-white/90">
            These roles help explain the growing scientific and clinical interest in NAD+ therapy. Human research on IV NAD+ is still developing, while the underlying biology and research on NAD+ precursors provide a strong foundation for continued study.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why IV Administration Section -->
  <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-white">
    <div class="section-shell">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
        <div class="rounded-2xl overflow-hidden shadow-xl order-2 lg:order-1">
          <img
            src="/images/treatments/nad-brain-clarity.webp"
            width="1200"
            height="821"
            loading="lazy"
            decoding="async"
            alt="Brain fog to mental clarity transformation with NAD+ therapy"
            class="w-full h-full object-cover"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="order-1 lg:order-2">
          <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-serif font-medium text-emerald-950 mb-6">Why IV Administration?</h2>
          <div class="prose prose-lg text-slate-600">
            <p>
              Oral NAD+ precursors such as NMN and NR must pass through the digestive system and be converted through several metabolic steps. IV NAD+ bypasses digestion and provides direct bloodstream delivery.
            </p>
            <p>
              This makes IV therapy appealing to patients who prefer a direct route, have difficulty with oral supplements or want a higher-dose option delivered over a defined appointment.
            </p>
            <p>
              NAD+ is infused gradually and the rate is tailored to comfort. The experience is usually relaxed, and patients can read, work quietly or watch something during the appointment.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pricing Section -->
  <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-emerald-50">
    <div class="section-shell">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
        <!-- NAD+ Therapy Card -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-3xl shadow-xl p-8 lg:p-10 card-hover">
          <div class="text-center mb-6">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-medium text-emerald-950 mb-4">NAD+ IV Therapy</h2>
            <div class="flex justify-center mb-4">
              <FlaskConical class="w-20 h-20 text-emerald-950" stroke-width={1.5} aria-hidden="true" />
            </div>
            <p class="text-slate-600">Cellular energy and healthy-aging support</p>
          </div>

          <ul class="space-y-3 mb-8">
            <li class="flex items-center">
              <Check class="w-5 h-5 text-emerald-600 mr-3 flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true" />
              <span>Pure NAD+ coenzyme</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-center">
              <Check class="w-5 h-5 text-emerald-600 mr-3 flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true" />
              <span>Direct bloodstream administration</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-center">
              <Check class="w-5 h-5 text-emerald-600 mr-3 flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true" />
              <span>Comfortable, gradual infusion</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-center">
              <Check class="w-5 h-5 text-emerald-600 mr-3 flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true" />
              <span>Personalized dose and schedule</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Getting Started Card -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-3xl shadow-xl p-8 lg:p-10 card-hover">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-medium text-emerald-950 mb-6">Getting Started with NAD+ Therapy</h2>

          <p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">
            To ensure that NAD+ therapy is appropriate for you, an initial naturopathic consultation is required. This allows us to review your health history, discuss your goals and create a personalized treatment plan.
          </p>

          <BookingButton variant="secondary" size="lg" fullWidth source="nad-therapy-pricing" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Research Evidence Section -->
  <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-white">
    <div class="section-shell">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-serif font-medium text-emerald-950 mb-6">The Science Behind NAD+</h2>
        <div class="prose prose-lg text-slate-600">
          <p>
            NAD+ research has expanded rapidly, with growing interest in cellular energy, metabolism, brain health and aging. Important findings include:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Cellular energy:</strong> NAD+ has a well-established role in mitochondrial energy metabolism and ATP production.<sup>1-3</sup></li>
            <li><strong>Cellular repair:</strong> NAD+ is required for sirtuins and PARP enzymes involved in metabolic regulation, stress response and DNA repair.<sup>1-3</sup></li>
            <li><strong>Healthy-aging research:</strong> Animal and human precursor studies have generated promising findings related to NAD+ metabolism, physical function and metabolic health.<sup>3-5</sup></li>
            <li><strong>IV experience:</strong> Early human research has begun to describe IV NAD+ administration, short-term laboratory markers and tolerability in clinical settings.<sup>6</sup></li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Research on IV NAD+ is earlier than the broader research on NAD+ biology and oral precursors. It is nevertheless a promising area, and IV therapy is available for patients who would like to explore it as part of an individualized health plan.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What to Expect Section -->
  <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-emerald-50">
    <div class="section-shell">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-serif font-medium text-emerald-950 mb-8 text-center">What to Expect</h2>

        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6 lg:gap-8">
          <div class="text-center">
            <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-emerald-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4">
              <span class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">1</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-emerald-950 mb-2">Before Your Infusion</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600">Eat a light meal, stay well hydrated and wear comfortable clothing with easy arm access. Bring something to read, watch or work on.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="text-center">
            <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-emerald-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4">
              <span class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">2</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-emerald-950 mb-2">During Your Infusion</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600">Sessions commonly take 1–4 hours depending on dose and infusion rate. Some people notice warmth, mild nausea or abdominal sensations that are usually managed by slowing the drip.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="text-center">
            <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-emerald-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4">
              <span class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">3</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-emerald-950 mb-2">After Your Infusion</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600">Most people resume their usual activities afterward. Many patients report increased energy or mental clarity within hours to days, although the timing and degree of response vary.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Safety Section -->
  <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-emerald-950">
    <div class="section-shell">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-serif font-medium text-white mb-6">Safety of NAD+ Therapy</h2>
        <div class="prose prose-lg prose-invert">
          <p class="text-white/90">
            NAD+ is a naturally occurring molecule and IV therapy has been used clinically for many years. Most patients tolerate it well when the infusion is given gradually and adjusted to their comfort.
          </p>
          <p class="text-white/90">
            The most common temporary effects are related to the infusion rate and may include warmth, nausea, abdominal discomfort or chest pressure. These sensations generally improve quickly when the infusion is slowed or paused.<sup>6</sup>
          </p>
          <p class="text-white/90">
            NAD+ therapy may not be appropriate during pregnancy or breastfeeding or with certain cardiac, kidney, cancer-related or other significant medical considerations. Your health history is reviewed before treatment.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <FAQSection bg="white" items={[
          { question: "How long does an NAD+ infusion take?", answer: "<p>NAD+ infusions commonly take 1–4 hours depending on the dose and your comfort with the infusion rate. We recommend bringing something to read, watch or work on during the appointment.</p>" },
          { question: "How many treatments will I need?", answer: "<p>Some patients begin with a short series of treatments and then decide whether occasional maintenance fits their goals. Your schedule is personalized according to your response, preferences and budget.</p>" },
          { question: "What does NAD+ therapy feel like?", answer: "<p>Many people find the appointment relaxing. Warmth, nausea or abdominal sensations can occur if the infusion is running too quickly and usually improve when the rate is slowed. Afterward, some patients report feeling more alert, energetic or mentally clear.</p>" },
          { question: "Is NAD+ therapy different from taking NAD+ supplements?", answer: "<p>Yes. Oral NAD+ products and precursors such as NMN or NR must be absorbed and metabolized through the digestive system. IV administration provides NAD+ directly into the bloodstream and allows the dose to be delivered gradually during one appointment.</p>" },
          { question: "Who should not receive NAD+ therapy?", answer: "<p>NAD+ therapy may not be appropriate during pregnancy or breastfeeding or for people with certain cardiac, kidney, cancer-related or other significant medical conditions. Your health history is reviewed before treatment.</p>" },
        ]} />

  <!-- References Section -->
  <section class="py-12 lg:py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="section-shell">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-serif font-medium text-emerald-950 mb-6">References</h2>
        <div class="text-slate-600 text-sm space-y-2">
          <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 space-y-1">
            <li>Yoshino J, Baur JA, Imai SI. NAD+ Intermediates: The Biology and Therapeutic Potential of NMN and NR. Cell Metab. 2018;27(3):513-528.</li>
            <li>Cantó C, Menzies KJ, Auwerx J. NAD(+) Metabolism and the Control of Energy Homeostasis: A Balancing Act between Mitochondria and the Nucleus. Cell Metab. 2015;22(1):31-53.</li>
            <li>Verdin E. NAD+ in aging, metabolism and neurodegeneration. Science. 2015;350(6265):1208-1213.</li>
            <li>Gindri IM, Ferrari G, Pinto LPS, et al. Evaluation of safety and effectiveness of NAD in different clinical conditions: a systematic review. Am J Physiol Endocrinol Metab. 2024;326(4):E417-E427.</li>
            <li>Li Y, et al. The therapeutic perspective of NAD+ precursors in age-related diseases. Cell Commun Signal. 2024;22:70.</li>
            <li>Reyna K, Heinzen G, Patel N, et al. Intravenous infusion of nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide (NAD+) versus nicotinamide riboside (NR): a retrospective tolerability pilot study in a real-world setting. Front Aging. 2026;7:1652582.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Section -->
  <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-emerald-950">
    <div class="section-shell text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-serif font-medium text-white mb-6">Ready to Explore NAD+ Therapy?</h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-emerald-200 max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-8">
        Book a consultation to discuss your goals and create a personalized NAD+ IV therapy plan.
      </p>
      <CTAButton source="nad-therapy-cta" />
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
